abstract: A REGISTRY LAW IN MICHIGAN.--New-York is not the only State in which a Registry takes effect, for the first time this Fall. abstract: The Anglo Saxon, whose news is telegraphed from Father Point, brings intelligence of the death of LEIGH HUNT. The veteran poet died in London, Aug. 28, in his 75th year. He was born at Southgate, in Middlesex, near London, Oct. 19, 1784. His father, who was a clergyman of the Angliean Church, was a native of the West Indies, and his mother was by birth a Philadelphian, and a relative of WEST, the painter.
